d and shaped. The volume explores the challenges which relate to the role of the consumer in the co-creation of the tourist experience, and the implications this has for the development, marketing, interpretation, consumption, planning and management of HSLT. It will appeal to researchers and students of heritage tourism, film and literary tourism, media-driven tourism, tourism planning and destination development and management.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aHeritage tourism. 0aLiterary journeys. 4aFILM, TV & RADIO. 4aMedia studies. 4aTourism industry. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Industries / Hospitality, Travel & Tourism.2bisacsh  aLiterary Tourism.  aScreen Tourism.  aService Dominant Logic.  aService-dominant logic.  aTourism.  aco-creation.  afilm tourism.  aheritage tourism.  atourist experience.  avalue creation .1 aShaw, Gareth, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCVP eBook-Package Contemporary 2016-2020z978311075434640uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978184541625640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781845416256423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781845416256.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK